# Linux Pipes and Redirection

## Commands

- |
- >
- >>
- tee

## Purpose

These commands allow administrators to combine commands, redirect output, and save results to files.

## Examples

```bash
ps aux | grep ssh

ls > files.txt

echo "Linux" >> notes.txt

ls | tee output.txt
```

## Best Practice

Use pipes to filter information instead of manually searching through command output.
